# Restoration question data.
# Records are separated by a blank line.
# choices use | as a separator. answer is zero-based and can be comma-separated.

id=easy-q-001
type=QUESTION
prompt=Which action usually restores soil health fastest after heavy erosion?
choices=Plant cover crops|Remove all plant roots|Compact the topsoil
answer=0
feedback.correct=Cover crops protect soil and rebuild organic matter.
feedback.wrong=The gate accepts the answer, but the land loses recovery time.

id=easy-q-002
type=QUESTION
prompt=Which energy source produces power directly from sunlight?
choices=Solar panels|Diesel generators|Coal furnaces
answer=0
feedback.correct=Solar power adds clean time to the reserve.
feedback.wrong=That choice keeps the old smoke in the system.

id=easy-d-001
type=DECISION
prompt=A settlement has leaking pipes and wants more water. What should be funded first?
choices=Repair leaks and monitor use|Pump more groundwater immediately|Ignore losses until the dry season
answer=0
feedback.correct=Fixing leaks restores capacity without exhausting the aquifer.
feedback.wrong=The decision moves forward, but the reserve shrinks.

id=easy-d-002
type=DECISION
prompt=You find a polluted canal beside a food market. Which first step has the least risk?
choices=Stop dumping and test the water|Add dye to hide the pollution|Open the canal into crop fields
answer=0
feedback.correct=Testing and source control buy the team clean time.
feedback.wrong=The gate opens, but the canal takes damage.
